SWNS/BoF Herring MSE MP Testing Draft Results GM MPs

2021-10-18

Summary of Results

Updates

Updates Since Version 1 (May 19, 2021):

Primary Updates:

  • The data inputs have been updated to include data up to 2020. These data are summarized here.

  • MPs submitted by the group have been included. Some other example MPs from Version 1 are also included.

  • The acoustic index in the projections is now assumed to be proportional to SSB. In Version 1, a hyperstability parameter was estimated from the historical data (observed acoustic index and model estimated SSB) that was less than 1 for most simulations. This hyperstability parameter was used to estimate the acoustic index in the projections in Version 1.

  • A new table was added showing the probability of the 3-yr moving average acoustic index being above the limit reference point of 318 kt in each of the first 15 years of the projections.

Minor Updates:

  • All performance metrics using the acoustic index are now based on the 3-yr moving average acoustic index.

  • The “average” performance is now is based on the median across all simulation and not the mean.

  • Trade-off plots now show the average performance of the most pessimistic, optimistic, and median OMs (instead of the 10th, 90th, and median across all simulations pooled across all OMs).

  • The results for the Robustness OMs have not been added yet.

Objectives

DRAFT

MSE Objectives

  • Maintain SSB above the minimum performance threshold
  • Maintain SSB above a target biomass in the long term
  • Maximize yield
  • Minimize variability in catch
  • Limit the removal of small fish

MP selection will also consider performance relative to the limit reference point in terms of the 3-yr moving average acoustic index

Performance Metrics

DRAFT

Performance Threshold

Threshold = 0.7SSBMSY (dynamic)

  • P(SSB>0.7SSBMSY) > 75% in each year beginning in year 10 of the 25-year projection period

The performance threshold is used to eliminate MPs from further consideration

Performance Metrics

Objective Metric Timeframe
Maintain SSB above a target biomass in the long term P(SSB > SSBmsy) Years 16-25
Maximize short term yield Average Yield Years 1-5
Maximize long term yield Average Yield Years 6-25
Minimize variability in catch Average inter-annual variability in yield Years 1-25
Limit the removal of small fish % Small Fish (<23 cm) Years 1-15

These performance metrics are used to rank the performance of MPs and are not used to eliminate MPs from consideration. Note that SSBMSY represents a potential target used for ranking the performance of MPs.

The following additional performance metrics are presented:

  • P(SSB > SSB2007) and # years to reach this value in the projections
  • P(3-yr Moving Average Acoustic Index > 318 kt) and # years to reach this value in the projections
  • P(SSB > 0.7SSBMSY_static1990-2020) and # years to reach this value in the projections
  • P(SSB > 0.3SSB0_static1990-2020) and # years to reach this value in the projections

Other performance metrics (for ranking MPs) can be added upon request

    • include = include weir fleet

Robustness Set

Rob Set 1

DRAFT

Note: 6 robustness OMs have been submitted by the herring MSE group. Additional robustness OMs can be added upon request

Additional levels for:

  • Growth
    • 1% increase = 1% increase in weight at age in each year in the projections
    • step back = a step back in weight-at-age over time (i.e., weight-at-age in nth projected year is the weight at age from year 2020-n)
    • status quo = mean of last 3 years used in the projections (from Reference Set)
  • Recruitment
    • 90-15 = future recruitment based on recruitment deviations from 1990-2017 (from Reference Set)
    • 68-15 = future recruitment based on recruitment deviations from 1990-2017
    • 90% = future recruitment based on the lower 90% of historical recruitment deviations
  • Additional Catch
    • US fish = 10 - 20 kt of Canadian fish are harvested in the US winter fishery in all projections
    • High Weir = Weir catches in projections return to historical levels (20 - 40 kt)

Note: Assumed selectivity for the US catches is the purse seine fleet selectivity.

Description

DRAFT
MP Description
NFref F=0 Reference
SQ NA
MP_GM_01 submitted by group
MP_GM_02 submitted by group

Status Quo MP: an approximation of the status quo MP

SQ Modifications

Change minimum TAC to lower harvest rate below the minimum operational control point.

Example MP of form “MP _ TAC1 _ TAC2 _ Index1 _ Index2 _ X Year”

These MPs are modifications of the status quo MP by changing the position of the operational control points and the smoothing of the acoustic index:

  • TAC1 = lower control point for the TAC
  • TAC2 = upper control point for the TAC
  • Index1 = lower control point for the acoustic index
  • Index2 = upper control point for the acoustic index
  • X Year = number of years used in the moving average smoother for the acoustic index

Example “MP_20_60_318_425_3”
